{"type":"message","id":"ae0a1aba","parentId":"620dc308","timestamp":"2026-07-08T07:09:53.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_882323fb32bb4348bd0ce742","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"log","sessionId":"cool-cove","timeout":30000},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"log\", \"sessionId\": \"cool-cove\", \"timeout\": 30000}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783494582801,"responseId":"ufdNaqiDNquo-eQPmIGimQM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5856021e","parentId":"ae0a1aba","timestamp":"2026-07-08T07:09:53.567Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_882323fb32bb4348bd0ce742","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"IMAGE2_READY=file PATH=/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png"}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"cool-cove","total":1,"totalLines":1,"totalChars":103,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"OUT2=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/middle-managers-$(date +%s).png\" PROMPT2=\"Professional ...onal leadership theme\""},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783494593560}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d46b055","parentId":"5856021e","timestamp":"2026-07-08T07:10:26.945Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a7241b87c3c549418c23f348","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \"264468965\" image \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/skillweaver-1783494572.png\" \"AI agents are choking on too many tools. This fix cuts tokens by 99%.\n\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\n\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\n\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\n\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver. Instead of dumping all tools into context, it:\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\n\nThe numbers are wild:\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\n\nThe insight that stopped me:\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\n\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\n\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\n\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\n\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\"","env":{"TELEGRAM_USER_ID":"264468965"}},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \\\"264468965\\\" image \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/skillweaver-1783494572.png\\\" \\\"AI agents are choking on too many tools. This fix cuts tokens by 99%.\\n\\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\\n\\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\\n\\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\\n\\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver. Instead of dumping all tools into context, it:\\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\\n\\nThe numbers are wild:\\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\\n\\nThe insight that stopped me:\\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\\n\\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\\n\\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\\n\\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\\n\\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\\\"\", \"env\": {\"TELEGRAM_USER_ID\": \"264468965\"}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783494593584,"responseId":"w_dNavedAdSGkuwPrZTkkAM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"38a17a02","parentId":"5d46b055","timestamp":"2026-07-08T07:10:29.586Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a7241b87c3c549418c23f348","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480518656704057344/\nDISPLAY_NAME: Andrii Bidochko\nCHARS: 1175"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2483,"aggregated":"OK: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480518656704057344/\nDISPLAY_NAME: Andrii Bidochko\nCHARS: 1175","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783494629583}}
{"type":"message","id":"6291721d","parentId":"38a17a02","timestamp":"2026-07-08T07:11:21.789Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_abb78d57003b46138e0377e2","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# AI agents are choking on too many tools\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-08T07:10:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480518656704057344/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7480518656704057344\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1,175\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/skillweaver-1783494572.png\n\n## Post Body\n\nAI agents are choking on too many tools. This fix cuts tokens by 99%.\n\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\n\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\n\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\n\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver. Instead of dumping all tools into context, it:\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\n\nThe numbers are wild:\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\n\nThe insight that stopped me:\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\n\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\n\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\n\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\n\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-08-ai-agents-are-choking-on.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# AI agents are choking on too many tools\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-08T07:10:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480518656704057344/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7480518656704057344\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 1,175\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/skillweaver-1783494572.png\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\nAI agents are choking on too many tools. This fix cuts tokens by 99%.\\n\\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\\n\\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\\n\\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\\n\\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver. Instead of dumping all tools into context, it:\\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\\n\\nThe numbers are wild:\\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\\n\\nThe insight that stopped me:\\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\\n\\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\\n\\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\\n\\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\\n\\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-08-ai-agents-are-choking-on.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_60ec50f2a20a4cceab899e8c","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"enabled":true,"name":"Auto-publish LinkedIn post 2 - Middle Managers AI","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"PUBLISH_NOW: Use li-post.sh to publish this post with the image at /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\n\nPOST TEXT:\nYour middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\n\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\n\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\n\nMiddle managers are caught between:\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\n\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\n→ Tool selection and procurement\n→ Training and upskilling programs\n→ Change management across teams\n→ Security and compliance concerns\n→ Productivity expectations from above\n\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\n\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\n\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\n\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\n\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\n\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\n\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\n\nAfter publishing, save the post record to /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/","model":"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas"},"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-08T09:15:00Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"add\", \"job\": {\"delivery\": {\"mode\": \"none\"}, \"enabled\": true, \"name\": \"Auto-publish LinkedIn post 2 - Middle Managers AI\", \"payload\": {\"kind\": \"agentTurn\", \"message\": \"PUBLISH_NOW: Use li-post.sh to publish this post with the image at /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\\n\\nPOST TEXT:\\nYour middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\\n\\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\\n\\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\\n\\nMiddle managers are caught between:\\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\\n\\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\\n→ Tool selection and procurement\\n→ Training and upskilling programs\\n→ Change management across teams\\n→ Security and compliance concerns\\n→ Productivity expectations from above\\n\\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\\n\\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\\n\\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\\n\\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\\n\\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\\n\\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\\n\\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\\n\\nAfter publishing, save the post record to /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/\", \"model\": \"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas\"}, \"schedule\": {\"at\": \"2026-07-08T09:15:00Z\", \"kind\": \"at\"}, \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\"}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783494629599,"responseId":"5vdNapiFKOro3PQPjpGxsAg"}}
