{"type":"message","id":"7fa1956b","parentId":"74d1528a","timestamp":"2026-07-08T07:11:22.136Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_60ec50f2a20a4cceab899e8c","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"6623f276-1fe9-4efa-9c04-50f8fdc85630\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"name\": \"Auto-publish LinkedIn post 2 - Middle Managers AI\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1783494681973,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1783494681973,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"at\": \"2026-07-08T09:15:00.000Z\",\n    \"kind\": \"at\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"PUBLISH_NOW: Use li-post.sh to publish this post with the image at /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\\n\\nPOST TEXT:\\nYour middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\\n\\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\\n\\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\\n\\nMiddle managers are caught between:\\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\\n\\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\\n→ Tool selection and procurement\\n→ Training and upskilling programs\\n→ Change management across teams\\n→ Security and compliance concerns\\n→ Productivity expectations from above\\n\\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\\n\\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\\n\\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\\n\\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\\n\\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\\n\\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\\n\\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\\n\\nAfter publishing, save the post record to /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/\",\n    \"model\": \"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"none\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1783502100000\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"id":"6623f276-1fe9-4efa-9c04-50f8fdc85630","agentId":"main","name":"Auto-publish LinkedIn post 2 - Middle Managers AI","enabled":true,"deleteAfterRun":true,"createdAtMs":1783494681973,"updatedAtMs":1783494681973,"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-08T09:15:00.000Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"PUBLISH_NOW: Use li-post.sh to publish this post with the image at /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\n\nPOST TEXT:\nYour middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\n\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\n\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\n\nMiddle managers are caught between:\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\n\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\n→ Tool selection and procurement\n→ Training and upskilling programs\n→ Change management across teams\n→ Security and compliance concerns\n→ Productivity expectations from above\n\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\n\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\n\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\n\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\n\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\n\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\n\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\n\nAfter publishing, save the post record to /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/","model":"litellm/vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas"},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1783502100000}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783494682132}}
