**\n\nDefine the outcome. Make it measurable. Let the agent optimize toward it.\n\nEvery successful iteration is progress. Every failure is a signal. No guessing.\n\nTraditional software has tests. AI agents need benchmarks.\n\nWithout one, you're not building a system. You're building a feeling.\n\nWhat's your agent's benchmark — or are you hoping it figures itself out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering #TDD\n\n**Characters:** ~900\n\n---\n\n## Trend Proposals — 2026-07-03\n\n### Claude Fable 5 outage exposed a fatal gap: only 1 in 10 enterprises can auto-catch failing AI\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-lost-claude-fable-5-for-a-few-weeks-new-data-shows-two-thirds-had-already-built-their-hedge\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\" — You built an AI agent. It went down. Did you even notice? Most teams have no fallback detection. That's the real risk.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲.\n**Persona:** CTO at 200+ person company — running production AI, can't afford silent failures\n**Status:** ✍️ Writing now\n\n---\n\n### Trunk Tools cut document review from 60 days to 10 — by ditching general-purpose models\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The mistake most people will make\" — Most teams throw GPT-4 at everything. The winners are building specialized stacks that skip the bloat.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n**Persona:** CTO at IT consultancy — needs to deliver client projects faster with reusable components\n**Scheduled:** July 7, 2026 (Monday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### DeepSeek open-sourced DSpark — 85% faster LLM inference\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-open-sources-dspark-a-new-framework-to-speed-up-llm-inference-by-up-to-85\n**Published:** June 29, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — Inference costs are collapsing. If your AI strategy depends on one provider's pricing, you're overpaying. Open-source is eating the margin.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗜𝗻𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗮𝗽𝘀𝗲.\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — wants AI competitiveness without bleeding budget\n**Scheduled:** July 10, 2026 (Thursday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Morgan Stanley made its AI agents LESS autonomous — and cut riskiest job in half\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous\n**Published:** June 30, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"Contrarian take\" — Everyone's chasing fully autonomous agents. Morgan Stanley went the opposite direction — and won. Sometimes constraints beat freedom.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\n**Persona:** Enterprise Innovation Officer at financial services company — zero tolerance for error, needs reliable AI\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Restaurants now take orders from ChatGPT and Claude directly — no app, no setup\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\n**Published:** July 1, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — AI agents are now ordering dinner. Your customers will expect the same from your business. The question isn't if — it's how fast you can plug in.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — needs to stay competitive with AI integration\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n## Published Posts\n\n- 2026-07-06: Test-driven development changed how we write software (TDD ↔ Benchmark for AI Agents)\n- 2026-07-03: Alibaba just cut AI agent token use by 99%\n- 2026-06-25: Most companies are building AI backwards\n- 2026-06-25: AI isn't coming for your job\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783500236403}}
{"type":"message","id":"30227ab4","parentId":"abfcfcec","timestamp":"2026-07-08T08:44:04.631Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a46de81839da4892b8dfd04a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-coach/SKILL.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-coach/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783500236423,"responseId":"zg1OapZSiozp2A-Qu56QAw"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4a29fc1","parentId":"30227ab4","timestamp":"2026-07-08T08:44:04.665Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a46de81839da4892b8dfd04a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: linkedin-coach\ndescription: Proactive LinkedIn coach. Checks posting cadence, sends daily nudges, proposes next content idea. Run by cron or manually.\nuser-invocable: true\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"requires\":{\"env\":[\"LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID\"]}}}\ntriggers:\n  - \"coach me\"\n  - \"what should i post today\"\n  - \"am i on track\"\n  - \"linkedin check in\"\n  - \"how am i doing on linkedin\"\n  - \"push me to post\"\n  - \"content nudge\"\n---\n\n# LinkedIn Coach Skill\n\n> ⚠️ MANDATORY RULES:\n> 1. **Never publish.** This skill motivates and proposes. Posting uses `linkedin-publish`.\n> 2. **Per-user isolation.** All data keyed by `$TELEGRAM_USER_ID` (from env or cron prompt).\n> 3. **Always be a coach, not a reporter.** Don't just show stats — interpret them. Push the user to act.\n> 4. **DO NOT narrate steps.** Show results directly.\n\n---\n\n## When this skill runs\n\n- **Daily cron** (9 AM user timezone) — called with explicit `TELEGRAM_USER_ID` in prompt\n- **Heartbeat session** — owner gets a quick check each session\n- **User manually asks** — \"what should I post today?\", \"coach me\", etc.\n\n---\n\n## Flow: Daily Coach Check\n\n### Step 1 — Load user context (ONE bash block)\n\n```bash\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nBASE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\"\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\n\n# OAuth check\nACCESS_TOKEN=*** -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].display_name // \"there\"' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\n\n# Strategy: extract cadence line\nCADENCE=\"unknown\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/strategy.md\" ]; then\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \"cadence\\|frequency\\|per week\\|posts/week\" \"$BASE/strategy.md\" | head -1 | sed 's/.*: //')\nfi\n\n# Posts in last 7 days\nPOST_COUNT=$(find \"$BASE/posts/\" -name \"*.md\" -newer \"$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-7d +%Y-%m-%d)\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n\n# Days since last post\nLAST_POST_DATE=$(ls -t \"$BASE/posts/\"*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -oE '[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}')\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\n\n# Next calendar idea\nNEXT_IDEA=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/content-calendar.md\" ]; then\n  NEXT_IDEA=$(grep -A2 \"Status.*Planned\\|Status.*planned\\|\\[ \\]\" \"$BASE/content-calendar.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -5)\nfi\n\necho \"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\"\necho \"CADENCE=$CADENCE\"\necho \"POSTS_LAST_7=$POST_COUNT\"\necho \"LAST_POST=$LAST_POST_DATE\"\necho \"TODAY=$TODAY\"\necho \"NEXT_IDEA_BLOCK=$NEXT_IDEA\"\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Interpret and coach\n\nUse the output to pick one of these tones. Be direct, be human, be Gary Vee — not a status report bot.\n\n**If no token / not connected:**\nSkip this user silently (cron context) or route to onboarding (manual context).\n\n**If POSTS_LAST_7 = 0 and LAST_POST is > 7 days ago (or empty):**\n```\nHey <NAME> 👊\n\nYou haven't posted in over a week. That's the brand dying quietly.\n\nHere's the thing — your audience doesn't remember you if you're not showing up. One post this week is better than the perfect post next month.\n\n<NEXT_IDEA if available — frame as \"Here's your topic for today:\">\n\nReady to write it now?\n```\n\nSend with buttons (put the message text above in the top-level `message`\nfield — Telegram ignores text inside `presentation.blocks`):\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"<the coach message text above>\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"✍️ Write it now\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_write_now\" }, \"style\": \"primary\" },\n        { \"label\": \"💡 Give me another idea\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_new_idea\" } },\n        { \"label\": \"Later\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_later\" }, \"style\": \"secondary\" }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**If POSTS_LAST_7 >= 1 but below cadence target:**\n```\nHey <NAME> — you're posting, which is great. But you're a bit behind your <CADENCE> target this week (<POST_COUNT> posts so far).\n\nOne more push and you're on track. Here's a quick idea:\n\n<NEXT_IDEA>\n\nWant to knock it out now?\n```\n\nSame buttons.\n\n**If on track (meeting or exceeding cadence):**\n```\n<NAME> — you're showing up. <POST_COUNT> posts this week. That's the work.\n\nKeep the momentum. Here's what's up next in your calendar:\n\n<NEXT_IDEA>\n\nWrite it now or save it for later?\n```\n\nButtons (message text goes in the top-level `message` field):\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"<the coach message text above>\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"✍️ Write next post\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_write_now\" }, \"style\": \"primary\" },\n        { \"label\": \"💡 Suggest something else\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"coach_new_idea\" } }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — Handle button callbacks\n\n- `coach_write_now` → read the next calendar idea, pass topic to `linkedin-brand-voice` draft flow immediately\n- `coach_new_idea` → suggest 3 new topic ideas from their content pillars (read strategy.md for pillars), show as new buttons\n- `coach_later` → reply \"Got it. I'll check in tomorrow.\" and stop\n\n---\n\n## Flow: All-Users Cron Run\n\nUsed when cron fires without a specific TELEGRAM_USER_ID (broadcasts to all connected users).\n\n```bash\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\n[ -f \"$TOKEN_STORE\" ] || exit 0\n\n# Get all user IDs with a valid token\njq -r 'to_entries[] | select(.value.access_token != null and .value.access_token != \"\") | .key' \"$TOKEN_STORE\"\n```\n\nFor each user ID returned, run the **Daily Coach Check** flow above, sending a targeted Telegram DM to each user.\n\n---\n\n## Coaching principles (always apply)\n\n- **Never just report.** \"You posted 2 times\" is data. \"You're ahead of pace — keep going\" is coaching.\n- **One clear action.** Every message ends with a button or a direct question. No open-ended essays.\n- **Reference their strategy.** If they set a goal, hold them to it. Quote their own cadence back to them.\n- **Short messages win.** 3-5 lines max. This is a Telegram DM, not an email.\n- **Match Gary Vee energy.** Direct, urgent, no excuses. But warm — you're rooting for them.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783500244661}}
{"type":"message","id":"d22901ff","parentId":"f4a29fc1","timestamp":"2026-07-08T08:44:16.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_88a4ef4ac7f84137922465f9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"UID=\"264468965\"\nBASE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\"\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\n\n# OAuth check\nACCESS_TOKEN=*** -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].display_name // \"there\"' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\n\n# Strategy: extract cadence line\nCADENCE=\"unknown\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/strategy.md\" ]; then\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \"cadence\\|frequency\\|per week\\|posts/week\" \"$BASE/strategy.md\" | head -1 | sed 's/.*: //')\nfi\n\n# Posts in last 7 days - count by date in filename\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nWEEK_AGO=$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-7d +%Y-%m-%d)\nPOST_COUNT=0\nif [ -d \"$BASE/posts/\" ]; then\n  for f in \"$BASE/posts/\"*.md; do\n    [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n    FDATE=$(basename \"$f\" | grep -oE '^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}')\n    if [ -n \"$FDATE\" ] && [ \"$FDATE\" \\> \"$WEEK_AGO\" ]; then\n      POST_COUNT=$((POST_COUNT + 1))\n    fi\n  done\nfi\n\n# Days since last post\nLAST_POST_DATE=$(ls -t \"$BASE/posts/\"*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -oE '[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}')\n\necho \"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\"\necho \"CADENCE=$CADENCE\"\necho \"POSTS_LAST_7=$POST_COUNT\"\necho \"LAST_POST=$LAST_POST_DATE\"\necho \"TODAY=$TODAY\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"UID=\\\"264468965\\\"\\nBASE=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\\\"\\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\\n\\n# OAuth check\\nACCESS_TOKEN=$(jq -r --arg u \\\"$UID\\\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \\\"$TOKEN_STORE\\\" 2>/dev/null)\\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \\\"$UID\\\" '.[$u].display_name // \\\"there\\\"' \\\"$TOKEN_STORE\\\" 2>/dev/null)\\n\\n# Strategy: extract cadence line\\nCADENCE=\\\"unknown\\\"\\nif [ -f \\\"$BASE/strategy.md\\\" ]; then\\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \\\"cadence\\\\|frequency\\\\|per week\\\\|posts/week\\\" \\\"$BASE/strategy.md\\\" | head -1 | sed 's/.*: //')\\nfi\\n\\n# Posts in last 7 days - count by date in filename\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nWEEK_AGO=$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-7d +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPOST_COUNT=0\\nif [ -d \\\"$BASE/posts/\\\" ]; then\\n  for f in \\\"$BASE/posts/\\\"*.md; do\\n    [ -f \\\"$f\\\" ] || continue\\n    FDATE=$(basename \\\"$f\\\" | grep -oE '^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}')\\n    if [ -n \\\"$FDATE\\\" ] && [ \\\"$FDATE\\\" \\\\> \\\"$WEEK_AGO\\\" ]; then\\n      POST_COUNT=$((POST_COUNT + 1))\\n    fi\\n  done\\nfi\\n\\n# Days since last post\\nLAST_POST_DATE=$(ls -t \\\"$BASE/posts/\\\"*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -oE '[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}')\\n\\necho \\\"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\\\"\\necho \\\"CADENCE=$CADENCE\\\"\\necho \\\"POSTS_LAST_7=$POST_COUNT\\\"\\necho \\\"LAST_POST=$LAST_POST_DATE\\\"\\necho \\\"TODAY=$TODAY\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783500244679,"responseId":"1g1OasPsEb-S6dgPqeLdoAI"}}
