nYou pick a model. Then you try to make it do EVERYTHING. Summarization. Extraction. Classification. Generation. One tool, all jobs.\\n\\nThat's not a strategy. That's a crutch.\\n\\nThe winners are doing the opposite. They're building specialized stacks:\\n→ Small models for simple tasks (fast, cheap)\\n→ Domain-specific fine-tunes for niche work\\n→ General-purpose models ONLY when nothing else fits\\n\\nThe result? 6x faster. 80% less spend. Better accuracy.\\n\\nYou don't need a bigger model. You need the RIGHT model for each job.\\n\\nWhat's one task you're overpaying to run?\\n\\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AIArchitecture #Efficiency\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Trunk Tools cut document review (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-09-2\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-09-2\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-09-2\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783556142754,"responseId":"MOhOarHOI9ah-eQPic3vqAE"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7af5b3f2-da4e-4bad-b9e5-38beb084e72e","parentId":"f0041038","timestamp":"2026-07-09T00:15:50.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n\nTrunk Tools just cut document review from 60 days to 10.\n\nTheir secret? They stopped throwing GPT-4 at everything.\n\nHere's the mistake most teams make:\n\nYou pick a model. Then you try to make it do EVERYTHING. Summarization. Extraction. Classification. Generation. One tool, all jobs.\n\nThat's not a strategy. That's a crutch.\n\nThe winners are doing the opposite. They're building specialized stacks:\n→ Small models for simple tasks (fast, cheap)\n→ Domain-specific fine-tunes for niche work\n→ General-purpose models ONLY when nothing else fits\n\nThe result? 6x faster. 80% less spend. Better accuracy.\n\nYou don't need a bigger model. You need the RIGHT model for each job.\n\nWhat's one task you're overpaying to run?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AIArchitecture #Efficiency\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Trunk Tools cut document review (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783556150820,"idempotencyKey":"4f84c603-0a30-4364-a7b6-3ede0ba18962:message-tool:mKqcH3YI1xjJJ5WCaaSRELYa:call_455b2f1668a34b379d2aa6e1"}}
