{"type":"message","id":"902d5307","parentId":"0e68a9ca","timestamp":"2026-07-09T00:15:58.520Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1198633f941543809dd48efc","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\n\nEveryone's chasing fully autonomous AI agents. Self-driving workflows. Zero human input.\n\nMorgan Stanley went the opposite direction. And it worked.\n\nTheir riskiest reconciliation job? Cut in half. Not by giving agents MORE freedom. By giving them constraints.\n\nHere's the insight most teams miss:\n\nAutonomy isn't a feature. It's a risk multiplier.\n\nThe more freedom an agent has, the more ways it can fail. The harder it is to debug. The less predictable the output.\n\nMorgan Stanley didn't dumb down their AI. They made it focused. Scoped. Accountable.\n\nThe result? Fewer errors. Faster resolution. Actual trust from the humans in the loop.\n\nSometimes the best AI architecture is knowing when to say \"stop, ask a human.\"\n\nAre your agents autonomous — or just unsupervised?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #FinancialServices #Automation\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Morgan Stanley made agents less autonomous (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-09-3"},"label":"✅ Publish now","style":"success"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-09-3"},"label":"✏️ Edit first"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-09-3"},"label":"⏭️ Skip","style":"secondary"}],"type":"buttons"}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\\n\\nEveryone's chasing fully autonomous AI agents. Self-driving workflows. Zero human input.\\n\\nMorgan Stanley went the opposite direction. And it worked.\\n\\nTheir riskiest reconciliation job? Cut in half. Not by giving agents MORE freedom. By giving them constraints.\\n\\nHere's the insight most teams miss:\\n\\nAutonomy isn't a feature. It's a risk multiplier.\\n\\nThe more freedom an agent has, the more ways it can fail. The harder it is to debug. The less predictable the output.\\n\\nMorgan Stanley didn't dumb down their AI. They made it focused. Scoped. Accountable.\\n\\nThe result? Fewer errors. Faster resolution. Actual trust from the humans in the loop.\\n\\nSometimes the best AI architecture is knowing when to say \\\"stop, ask a human.\\\"\\n\\nAre your agents autonomous — or just unsupervised?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #FinancialServices #Automation\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Morgan Stanley made agents less autonomous (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-09-3\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-09-3\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-09-3\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783556150942,"responseId":"OOhOasSPNKuo-eQPmIGimQM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"82779ad8-6e6a-414c-a2fb-01543190ab88","parentId":"902d5307","timestamp":"2026-07-09T00:15:58.850Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\n\nEveryone's chasing fully autonomous AI agents. Self-driving workflows. Zero human input.\n\nMorgan Stanley went the opposite direction. And it worked.\n\nTheir riskiest reconciliation job? Cut in half. Not by giving agents MORE freedom. By giving them constraints.\n\nHere's the insight most teams miss:\n\nAutonomy isn't a feature. It's a risk multiplier.\n\nThe more freedom an agent has, the more ways it can fail. The harder it is to debug. The less predictable the output.\n\nMorgan Stanley didn't dumb down their AI. They made it focused. Scoped. Accountable.\n\nThe result? Fewer errors. Faster resolution. Actual trust from the humans in the loop.\n\nSometimes the best AI architecture is knowing when to say \"stop, ask a human.\"\n\nAre your agents autonomous — or just unsupervised?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #FinancialServices #Automation\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Morgan Stanley made agents less autonomous (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783556158689,"idempotencyKey":"4f84c603-0a30-4364-a7b6-3ede0ba18962:message-tool:oq0ptS_VdIzn5gbDO94GF9QT:call_1198633f941543809dd48efc"}}
