{"type":"message","id":"21814f11","parentId":"0d886858","timestamp":"2026-07-10T06:44:31.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8cd53f64299b44fe87badd6b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1211 Jul  9 00:15 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-09-draft-1.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1178 Jul  9 00:15 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-09-draft-2.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1294 Jul  9 00:15 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-09-draft-3.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1211 Jul  9 00:15 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-09-draft-1.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1178 Jul  9 00:15 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-09-draft-2.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1294 Jul  9 00:15 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-09-draft-3.md","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783665871062}}
{"type":"message","id":"056136b7","parentId":"21814f11","timestamp":"2026-07-10T06:45:19.417Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e92e622ce30e4e8e9d280106","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 2026-07-10\nn: 1\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-lost-claude-fable-5-for-a-few-weeks-new-data-shows-two-thirds-had-already-built-their-hedge\nsource_date: 2026-07-03\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲.\n\nClaude Fable 5 went down for weeks. Only 1 in 10 enterprises had auto-failure detection.\n\nHere's the gap nobody's talking about.\n\nMost teams built their AI stack for happy paths:\n→ Model responds\n→ Agent completes task\n→ Everything works great\n\nBut what happens when the model goes down?\n\nSilent failures. Stuck workflows. Customers waiting. No alerts.\n\nThe enterprises that survived the outage had TWO things:\n1. Multi-model fallback (switch to GPT, Gemini, open-source)\n2. Health checks that actually ping the model — not just the API\n\nIf your monitoring says \"green\" but your agent is frozen, you don't have observability. You have a dashboard.\n\nThe real test: Can you detect a failure BEFORE your customers tell you?\n\nWhen did you last test your AI failure detection?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Reliability #EnterpriseAI #Monitoring\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-10-draft-1.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"---\\ndate: 2026-07-10\\nn: 1\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-lost-claude-fable-5-for-a-few-weeks-new-data-shows-two-thirds-had-already-built-their-hedge\\nsource_date: 2026-07-03\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲.\\n\\nClaude Fable 5 went down for weeks. Only 1 in 10 enterprises had auto-failure detection.\\n\\nHere's the gap nobody's talking about.\\n\\nMost teams built their AI stack for happy paths:\\n→ Model responds\\n→ Agent completes task\\n→ Everything works great\\n\\nBut what happens when the model goes down?\\n\\nSilent failures. Stuck workflows. Customers waiting. No alerts.\\n\\nThe enterprises that survived the outage had TWO things:\\n1. Multi-model fallback (switch to GPT, Gemini, open-source)\\n2. Health checks that actually ping the model — not just the API\\n\\nIf your monitoring says \\\"green\\\" but your agent is frozen, you don't have observability. You have a dashboard.\\n\\nThe real test: Can you detect a failure BEFORE your customers tell you?\\n\\nWhen did you last test your AI failure detection?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Reliability #EnterpriseAI #Monitoring\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-10-draft-1.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_da4dc7516786425ba33b92ae","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 2026-07-10\nn: 2\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\nsource_date: 2026-07-01\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\n\nThis is the new normal.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\n→ Book your service\n→ Buy your product\n→ Schedule a meeting\n→ Get support\n\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\n\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\n\nThe question isn't \"should we support AI transactions?\" It's \"how fast can we plug in?\"\n\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\n\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-10-draft-2.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"---\\ndate: 2026-07-10\\nn: 2\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\\nsource_date: 2026-07-01\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\\n\\nRestaurants now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude. No app. No setup. Just AI-to-business transactions.\\n\\nThis is the new normal.\\n\\nYour customers will expect the same. They'll ask their AI assistant to:\\n→ Book your service\\n→ Buy your product\\n→ Schedule a meeting\\n→ Get support\\n\\nCan your business handle an AI customer?\\n\\nMost companies are still optimizing for human clicks. Meanwhile, AI agents are becoming the new interface.\\n\\nThe question isn't \\\"should we support AI transactions?\\\" It's \\\"how fast can we plug in?\\\"\\n\\nIf a restaurant can do it with zero setup, what's stopping you?\\n\\n#AI #Ecommerce #DigitalTransformation #FutureOfBusiness #AIAgents\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-10-draft-2.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_58527497767f408c85b20be0","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 2026-07-10\nn: 3\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: internal\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴. 𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲'𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\n\nEveryone's chasing the most autonomous, most intelligent, most powerful AI agent.\n\nBut the teams shipping real value? They're doing the opposite.\n\nThey're building BORING agents:\n→ One clear task\n→ Defined success criteria\n→ Human in the loop for edge cases\n→ Fails gracefully, not spectacularly\n\nBoring means predictable. Predictable means trustworthy. Trustworthy means adoption.\n\nThe flashiest AI demo you saw last week? Probably broken in production.\n\nThe boring agent that just works? That's the one getting renewed.\n\nStop optimizing for impressive. Start optimizing for reliable.\n\nWhat's the most boring AI agent you could ship this week?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #SoftwareEngineering #Reliability\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-10-draft-3.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"---\\ndate: 2026-07-10\\nn: 3\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: internal\\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴. 𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲'𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\\n\\nEveryone's chasing the most autonomous, most intelligent, most powerful AI agent.\\n\\nBut the teams shipping real value? They're doing the opposite.\\n\\nThey're building BORING agents:\\n→ One clear task\\n→ Defined success criteria\\n→ Human in the loop for edge cases\\n→ Fails gracefully, not spectacularly\\n\\nBoring means predictable. Predictable means trustworthy. Trustworthy means adoption.\\n\\nThe flashiest AI demo you saw last week? Probably broken in production.\\n\\nThe boring agent that just works? That's the one getting renewed.\\n\\nStop optimizing for impressive. Start optimizing for reliable.\\n\\nWhat's the most boring AI agent you could ship this week?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #SoftwareEngineering #Reliability\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-10-draft-3.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783665871106,"responseId":"0ZRQasLIIMiGkuwP06bUqAY"}}
